Roles & Responsibilities
Job Summary

Are you a seasoned Data Architect looking for a new challenge? Our client in the financial industry is seeking a dynamic and innovative professional to lead their enterprise-wide digital transformation projects. As the Data Architect, you will have the opportunity to revolutionize the current data architecture and build a cutting-edge next generation data platform that will drive the company's growth. If you have a passion for data and the drive to take on a leadership role in a dynamic industry, this is the opportunity for you!

Mandatory Skill-set
Degree in Data Engineering, Computer Science, Information Technology;
At least 10 years of experience in data architecture, preferably in a leadership role;
Experience in Data Engineering, Analytics and AI/ML;
Experience with the cloud (e.g. AWS , GCP );
Strong hands-on exposure with ETL Extract, Transform, Load tools;
Familiar with data technologies such as Operational Data Store, Data Lake and Data Warehouse;
Has experience in designing data patterns to support micro-service based application architecture;
Experience implementing batch and streaming data pipelines;
Knowledge of both SQL and NoSQL databases, including performance tuning and troubleshooting;
Worked on Data engineering tools and frameworks such as Airflow, Kafka, Hadoop, Spark, Beam, Flink, Kubernetes;
Exposure to Data as a Service concepts and data virtualization tools (e.g. Tableau/Qlik);
Experience with agile methodologies, technology-savvy and appreciates new modern web application technologies stacks;
Strong communication and technical documentation skills.
Desired Skill-set
Experience working with very large data sets, data analytics and machine learning;
Prior experience on Big Data and Machine learning.
Responsibilities
Take on a broad role within the Data & AI solution space, focusing on engineering big data platforms and data solutions;
Design data solutions that align with business priorities and drive value;
Collaborate with data science and data engineering teams to identify and pilot use cases for data transformation;
Engage with business teams to discuss use case feasibility and architectural design, translating business leaders' vision into feasible technical implementations while identifying misaligned initiatives;
Gather inputs from various stakeholders, including business users, data scientists, security professionals, data engineers, analysts, and IT operations, to align technical implementations with current and future requirements;
Contribute to defining the Data & AI solution architecture and selecting suitable technologies, ensuring seamless integration with existing data management and analytics tools;
Lead quality assurance (QA) activities throughout the design and implementation phases of Data & AI solutions;
Evaluate data tools and practices across data, models, and software engineering, focusing on continuous improvement and establishing feedback mechanisms for assessing data & AI services;
Collaborate closely with security and technology risk leaders to anticipate and mitigate risks, staying informed about upcoming regulations and aligning them with best practices.
